# Integration test: Apple Lisa 2 — Lisa Office System 3.1 boot to the Install menu
#
# Boots the Lisa 2 (rev-H boot ROM) from the LOS 3.1 install floppy (Disk 1) and
# verifies it reaches the Install/Repair/Restore menu.
# This exercises the full Lisa stack end to end:
#   - boot ROM RAM sizing + segment-MMU setup, OS load off the Sony 400K floppy;
#   - the FDC / VBL interrupt path that wakes the FS reader (the $C05F drive-done
#     encoding and the edge-latched VBL);
#   - the MC68000 custom segment MMU with per-process domains;
#   - demand-loading SYSTEM.SHELL + its ~25 code segments via group-0 bus errors
#     (the demand-segment fault contract: fetch faults recover by re-fetching,
#     RTS faults recover by re-executing — both saved-PC cases the OS BUS_ERR
#     handler relies on).
# The installer shell renders the menu by ~i=33M and then idles polling for a
# mouse click; a fixed 80M-instruction budget reaches a stable menu
# deterministically (the framebuffer is identical from ~48M onward).

scheduler.run 80000000

assert machine.id == "lisa" "machine.id != lisa"
assert machine.rom.checksum == "098917B2" "rom.checksum != 098917B2 (rev-H)"
assert machine.screen.width == 720 "screen.width != 720"
assert machine.screen.height == 364 "screen.height != 364"

# Verify the LOS 3.1 Install/Repair/Restore menu matches the reference:
#   "Lisa 7/7  Office System 3.0  (c)1983, 1984 apple computer, inc."
#   "This micro diskette is used to repair the Lisa Office System startup disk
#    and to install the startup software. ..."
#   buttons: Finished / Repair / Install / Restore.
machine.screen.match expected.png

quit
